      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for the house i'm buying in toronto. i've never heard of that before... what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, setting up an escrow account is like preparing a treasure chest for your new home, but instead of gold and jewels, you're safeguarding the keys to your castle. In the world of real estate, an escrow account is a secure holding place for the money you're paying for your new abode. It's like a trusty goblin guard, ensuring that your hard-earned coins don't fall into the wrong hands before the deal is sealed. This way, the seller and the buyer can both feel confident that the transaction is fair and square, with no goblin sneaking in to steal the treasure. So, think of it as a magical barrier that protects both parties until the closing ceremony, when the keys to your new home are finally handed over.",
